WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:02.044
Baba. my love…

2
00:00:02.127 --> 00:00:03.128
<i>forgive me.</i>

3
00:00:03.212 --> 00:00:05.380
Yesterday. I was mourning my mother.

4
00:00:05.464 --> 00:00:07.508
Today. she is a living princess.

5
00:00:07.591 --> 00:00:09.801
This marriage will serve us all.

6
00:00:10.302 --> 00:00:12.638
So. this is Pennsa?
Is it always this quiet?

7
00:00:12.721 --> 00:00:13.722
Never.

8
00:00:13.805 --> 00:00:14.973
I am last of the Alkenny.

9
00:00:15.057 --> 00:00:17.142
Bow!

10
00:00:17.226 --> 00:00:18.477
Mom!

11
00:00:19.019 --> 00:00:21.647
- How can you be getting married today?
- I can't stop this.

12
00:00:21.730 --> 00:00:24.358
Princess Maghra and Lord Harlan.

13
00:00:24.441 --> 00:00:26.652
you may seal your union.

14
00:00:26.735 --> 00:00:30.989
I will convince the council to request
a diplomatic summit with the Payans.

15
00:00:31.073 --> 00:00:32.658
Trivantians do not sue for peace!

16
00:00:32.741 --> 00:00:35.077
It will give us time
to bring a battalion or two east.

17
00:00:35.160 --> 00:00:36.578
We need you to cross the border.

18
00:00:36.662 --> 00:00:38.264
- What's the cargo?
- Her daughter.

19
00:00:38.288 --> 00:00:40.082
Consider it a wedding gift.

20
00:00:40.165 --> 00:00:42.668
Many good things start with desire.

21
00:00:42.751 --> 00:00:44.391
- You cannot trust her.
- Why not?

22
00:00:44.461 --> 00:00:46.797
She's not the one
who lied to me my entire life.

23
00:00:46.880 --> 00:00:48.924
From this place. it's two days to Pennsa.

24
00:00:49.007 --> 00:00:50.634
What do you think she'll be like?

25
00:00:50.717 --> 00:00:51.945
She'll be like Maghra.

26
00:00:51.969 --> 00:00:53.449
Do we even know who that is?

27
00:00:55.000 --> 00:01:01.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

28
00:01:02.335 --> 00:01:04.379
Thank you for coming to me.

29
00:01:04.462 --> 00:01:08.216
Ladies. lords.
Thank you for your pledges of support.

30
00:01:08.299 --> 00:01:10.385
Captain Gosset. how goes the count?

31
00:01:11.219 --> 00:01:14.889
Our outposts at Hareburr and Currlye
have pledged 25 soldiers.

32
00:01:14.973 --> 00:01:17.433
Lebnin has pledged an additional 30.

33
00:01:17.517 --> 00:01:22.272
Lebnin considers it an honor.
not just a duty. Your Majesty.

34
00:01:22.772 --> 00:01:26.651
I stand with you.
as my father stood with your father.

35
00:01:28.236 --> 00:01:29.797
When we combine that
with our Pennsan troops...

36
00:01:29.821 --> 00:01:31.447
Ah. ah.

37
00:01:33.408 --> 00:01:37.495
Nothing from Altoona? Can that be so?

38
00:01:38.204 --> 00:01:40.290
Lord Diego. is it?

39
00:01:40.373 --> 00:01:44.586
Your Majesty. Altoona stands ready
with an additional 20 troops.

40
00:01:45.378 --> 00:01:47.338
Ten less than Lebnin.

41
00:01:48.590 --> 00:01:50.633
Your city is twice as populated.

42
00:01:50.717 --> 00:01:53.052
We are approaching the planting season.

43
00:01:53.136 --> 00:01:56.306
The town council felt that
the farmworkers must continue to plant.

44
00:01:56.389 --> 00:01:58.016
or we will face a shortage.

45
00:01:58.516 --> 00:02:03.354
Lord Diego. are you at all aware
of what transpired at Kanzua?

46
00:02:03.855 --> 00:02:06.107
We all heard tales of your suffering.

47
00:02:07.108 --> 00:02:11.279
Tell me. if I destroyed
your home in front of you.

48
00:02:12.405 --> 00:02:16.826
drowned everyone you knew and loved.
murdered your wife and your children.

49
00:02:17.452 --> 00:02:19.078
would you be worried about crops?

50
00:02:20.955 --> 00:02:22.624
My apologies. Your Highness.

51
00:02:22.707 --> 00:02:26.294
Perhaps we should
go to Altoona and find out.

52
00:02:27.420 --> 00:02:28.421
Hmm?

53
00:02:29.714 --> 00:02:31.775
<i>The Trivantians made contact.
They wish to meet.</i>

54
00:02:31.799 --> 00:02:34.594
Lord Diego. I ask again.
How many troops do you pledge?

55
00:02:36.763 --> 00:02:39.224
Thirty troops. my queen.

56
00:02:42.227 --> 00:02:43.228
Very well.

57
00:02:46.856 --> 00:02:48.274
Captain Gosset?

58
00:02:48.358 --> 00:02:51.110
The count continues
with chambers in Monroe.

59
00:02:53.112 --> 00:02:55.949
Do you ever imagine
the fire is speaking to you?

60
00:02:57.450 --> 00:03:01.204
When I was alone after Father died
and you disappeared.

61
00:03:02.038 --> 00:03:04.414
I swore it told me secrets.

62
00:03:06.626 --> 00:03:09.921
Why didn't you tell me
Trivantes requested a diplomatic summit?

63
00:03:10.004 --> 00:03:11.381
Because it doesn't matter.

64
00:03:12.966 --> 00:03:14.717
Imagine Father's reaction.

65
00:03:15.593 --> 00:03:20.098
The mighty Triangle frightened of me.
Begging me for peace.

66
00:03:20.181 --> 00:03:22.725
- We have to consider it.
- Why?

67
00:03:23.852 --> 00:03:27.480
We have righteousness on our side.
God leading the charge.

68
00:03:27.564 --> 00:03:32.819
Yeah. well. even so. on the battlefield.
the men must believe.

69
00:03:32.902 --> 00:03:34.988
- In God?
- In you.

70
00:03:36.447 --> 00:03:40.618
They must believe that their queen did
everything in her power to protect them.

71
00:03:42.579 --> 00:03:44.414
My men will do as they're commanded.

72
00:03:45.582 --> 00:03:46.583
Sibeth.

73
00:03:48.543 --> 00:03:52.297
A soldier must believe in his cause.
must believe in his queen.

74
00:03:52.380 --> 00:03:55.842
must love her to the point
that he would be willing to die for her.

75
00:03:58.720 --> 00:04:04.642
Imagine if you could stop Trivantes
from encroaching on our land

76
00:04:04.726 --> 00:04:07.896
without sacrificing a single soldier.

77
00:04:09.105 --> 00:04:11.274
You already have their obedience.

78
00:04:11.357 --> 00:04:14.777
but if you manage this.
you would have their love.

79
00:04:17.947 --> 00:04:19.324
It's never been done.

80
00:04:20.408 --> 00:04:23.703
Well. when was the last time
the Trivantians asked for a parley?

81
00:04:24.787 --> 00:04:26.873
- Never.
- That's right.

82
00:04:29.292 --> 00:04:31.961
Maybe having God on your side means…

83
00:04:33.171 --> 00:04:37.008
you win the war
without having to fight the battle.

84
00:04:48.728 --> 00:04:51.022
The Trivantians have no queen or king.

85
00:04:51.105 --> 00:04:53.566
I cannot negotiate
with common politicians.

86
00:04:53.650 --> 00:04:55.235
Of course not.

87
00:04:56.402 --> 00:04:59.322
But I can go as your emissary.

88
00:04:59.822 --> 00:05:03.076
As the princess and as your sister.
I can speak for you.

89
00:05:10.291 --> 00:05:11.292
Very well.

90
00:05:18.091 --> 00:05:20.051
Thank you. Sibeth.

91
00:05:23.346 --> 00:05:27.058
Of course.
any treaty will require a formal apology

92
00:05:27.559 --> 00:05:30.687
and reparations for the attack on Kanzua.

93
00:05:31.271 --> 00:05:35.275
What? You know that's not possible.

94
00:05:37.193 --> 00:05:42.031
We're going to win a war
without fighting a battle. are we not?

95
00:05:42.991 --> 00:05:45.243
I would say anything is possible.

96
00:07:13.414 --> 00:07:16.209
So you thought
your wife was dead. but she wasn't.

97
00:07:16.292 --> 00:07:18.253
and now you're about to be together again.

98
00:07:18.336 --> 00:07:22.257
You must be so excited.
I'm excited. and I've never even met her.

99
00:07:22.340 --> 00:07:25.009
Of course. it's complicated
now that she's a princess.

100
00:07:25.093 --> 00:07:26.427
Strange. isn't it?

101
00:07:26.511 --> 00:07:30.056
That she never once thought to mention
that she was a princess.

102
00:07:30.139 --> 00:07:33.268
It's hard not to think of an omission
like that as a lie of sorts.

103
00:07:33.351 --> 00:07:36.980
Ooh. if I were you. I'd be thinking
the entire relationship was a lie.

104
00:07:37.063 --> 00:07:38.773
But you did raise two children together.

105
00:07:38.857 --> 00:07:41.401
It would be hard
to lie through all of that.

106
00:07:41.484 --> 00:07:44.946
I imagine if I were you.
I'd be very angry.

107
00:07:45.029 --> 00:07:49.492
Also. confused and nervous.
But also so happy that she's alive.

108
00:07:49.993 --> 00:07:52.328
Oh. I suppose I wouldn't know how to feel.

109
00:07:52.412 --> 00:07:54.914
What do I know?
I've never even been in love.

110
00:07:55.748 --> 00:07:58.418
Maybe that's 'cause you talk too much.

111
00:08:20.815 --> 00:08:22.442
I. uh... I think it's dead.

112
00:08:28.448 --> 00:08:30.408
I could. uh... I could run drills with you.

113
00:08:31.826 --> 00:08:33.953
See how you do with something alive.

114
00:08:37.624 --> 00:08:39.626
I only fight soldiers.

115
00:08:40.585 --> 00:08:42.629
And bales of hay. apparently.

116
00:08:43.296 --> 00:08:45.465
Come on. It'll be fun. We...

117
00:08:49.552 --> 00:08:50.553
You're right.

118
00:08:51.262 --> 00:08:54.140
That was exhilarating. Thank you.

119
00:09:08.112 --> 00:09:10.156
I'm not going to risk the wrath
of the princess

120
00:09:10.240 --> 00:09:13.701
by putting a scratch on her boy.

121
00:09:14.953 --> 00:09:17.914
Now. go away.

122
00:09:24.546 --> 00:09:25.547
Toad!

123
00:09:31.177 --> 00:09:32.804
I couldn't save my sister.

124
00:09:35.223 --> 00:09:36.723
I couldn't help my dad.

125
00:09:39.060 --> 00:09:41.521
I need to be able to defend my family.

126
00:09:43.064 --> 00:09:45.316
I'm too used to having
other people do it for me.

127
00:09:48.152 --> 00:09:51.114
I'm sure the princess can appoint you
a proper trainer.

128
00:09:52.282 --> 00:09:54.951
You're right. I'll ask her to appoint you.

129
00:10:04.711 --> 00:10:06.087
And why me?

130
00:10:07.255 --> 00:10:09.007
Because we get along so well.

131
00:10:11.342 --> 00:10:13.136
I'm done training for the day.

132
00:10:27.275 --> 00:10:30.862
- General. sir.
- Lieutenant. come.

133
00:10:43.124 --> 00:10:45.460
- It's sharp.
- Yeah.

134
00:10:46.920 --> 00:10:49.714
Virgin steel.
Put through a new forging process.

135
00:10:50.924 --> 00:10:54.302
Wielded properly. it won't be stopped.

136
00:10:55.136 --> 00:10:57.305
I'm rearming the entire battalion.

137
00:10:59.933 --> 00:11:00.934
Here.

138
00:11:02.977 --> 00:11:04.896
This one is yours.

139
00:11:06.648 --> 00:11:07.649
I don't understand.

140
00:11:07.732 --> 00:11:11.361
Didn't the Triangle offer the Payans
an overture for peace?

141
00:11:13.821 --> 00:11:15.907
The queen doesn't
falsely accuse another nation

142
00:11:15.990 --> 00:11:18.159
unless she is looking for a fight.

143
00:11:18.243 --> 00:11:21.412
The peace talks will fail.
and we will make sure they do.

144
00:11:21.496 --> 00:11:24.958
You have been very vocal
with the Triangle.

145
00:11:25.667 --> 00:11:28.503
If something goes wrong.
they will lay the blame at your feet.

146
00:11:28.586 --> 00:11:30.839
Which is why you will go in my place.

147
00:11:33.591 --> 00:11:38.888
If there's a chance for peace with Paya.
shouldn't we try for it?

148
00:11:39.681 --> 00:11:42.725
As it is. we're overcommitted
on the western front fighting the Ganites.

149
00:11:42.809 --> 00:11:43.810
Wren.

150
00:11:47.647 --> 00:11:48.648
Wren.

151
00:11:49.649 --> 00:11:54.070
The Payan queen has grown bold.
She's forgotten who we are.

152
00:11:55.488 --> 00:12:01.494
It is in the best interest of the republic
that we remind her.

153
00:12:20.054 --> 00:12:22.098
All right. This way. Stay close.

154
00:12:46.498 --> 00:12:48.041
It's Tamacti Jun.

155
00:12:52.962 --> 00:12:53.963
Wait here.

156
00:13:01.346 --> 00:13:02.347
Go.

157
00:13:05.308 --> 00:13:07.477
I told you to wait
while I gather intelligence.

158
00:13:07.560 --> 00:13:08.853
Is she here or not?

159
00:13:08.937 --> 00:13:12.774
Princess Maghra is here and safe for now.

160
00:13:13.566 --> 00:13:15.151
You're not telling us something.

161
00:13:16.277 --> 00:13:19.405
She's with the queen.
That's all I know for certain.

162
00:13:20.114 --> 00:13:21.199
And Kofun?

163
00:13:21.282 --> 00:13:23.034
I've heard nothing.

164
00:13:23.117 --> 00:13:26.496
His Witchfinder escort was traveling
without the benefit of compass maps.

165
00:13:26.579 --> 00:13:28.706
Perhaps we arrived first.

166
00:13:28.790 --> 00:13:29.874
Let's go find her.

167
00:13:29.958 --> 00:13:31.543
Seek out the highest house.

168
00:13:31.626 --> 00:13:33.503
The queen will
have fortified herself there.

169
00:13:33.586 --> 00:13:34.671
You're not coming?

170
00:13:35.171 --> 00:13:38.299
The queen thinks I'm dead.
which is how it will have to stay for now.

171
00:13:38.383 --> 00:13:40.718
I need to make contact
with those Witchfinders loyal to me

172
00:13:40.802 --> 00:13:43.054
and be assured of their continued service.

173
00:13:43.137 --> 00:13:46.015
We'll need their support
if we're gonna confront the queen.

174
00:13:47.433 --> 00:13:50.562
- And how will we find you?
- I'll find you when it's time.

175
00:13:52.230 --> 00:13:54.190
Tread lightly with the queen.

176
00:13:54.274 --> 00:13:58.403
She's unlike anyone you've ever known.
and you're in her realm now.

177
00:13:59.279 --> 00:14:00.530
I can handle myself.

178
00:14:00.613 --> 00:14:03.533
Yes. but less well without your head.

179
00:14:07.620 --> 00:14:09.289
I still don't trust him.

180
00:14:10.707 --> 00:14:14.836
I do not either.
But he has made no false steps yet.

181
00:14:16.421 --> 00:14:18.214
We cannot travel in such a big group.

182
00:14:18.298 --> 00:14:20.425
Paris. you stay here with Charlotte.

183
00:14:20.508 --> 00:14:24.179
- We'll send for you once we find her.
- I must stay close to keep Haniwa safe.

184
00:14:24.888 --> 00:14:27.724
And who has kept Haniwa safe
for the last 17 years?

185
00:14:28.224 --> 00:14:29.350
Here.

186
00:14:30.101 --> 00:14:31.436
Keep that safe.

187
00:14:33.771 --> 00:14:34.814
Carefully. Baba.

188
00:14:45.366 --> 00:14:46.868
That must be it.

189
00:14:59.422 --> 00:15:01.633
She'll be very happy that we're here.

190
00:15:04.010 --> 00:15:06.930
- She's a princess now.
- She's still Mom.

191
00:15:08.515 --> 00:15:12.727
What if she's not?
What if being here has changed her?

192
00:15:15.480 --> 00:15:17.023
Then we'll rescue her.

193
00:15:19.317 --> 00:15:20.318
Mmm.

194
00:15:29.536 --> 00:15:32.789
Two guards. Six steps.

195
00:15:33.289 --> 00:15:34.999
Guards. six steps.

196
00:15:42.257 --> 00:15:43.591
Identify yourself.

197
00:15:44.551 --> 00:15:46.052
I'm here for Princess Maghra.

198
00:15:46.135 --> 00:15:48.263
The princess does not
receive visitors at the palace.

199
00:15:48.346 --> 00:15:49.347
Move on.

200
00:15:49.973 --> 00:15:52.100
- She'll receive me.
- I said. move on!

201
00:15:57.522 --> 00:15:59.524
Haniwa!

202
00:16:01.985 --> 00:16:03.528
- Maghra!
- Mama!

203
00:16:03.611 --> 00:16:05.154
Stop!

204
00:16:06.698 --> 00:16:09.409
Dad! Dad!

205
00:16:11.786 --> 00:16:12.871
Stop!

206
00:16:14.247 --> 00:16:15.456
Stand down.

207
00:16:23.214 --> 00:16:24.215
Baba?

208
00:16:25.008 --> 00:16:27.260
No. A bear.

209
00:16:27.760 --> 00:16:31.139
I found you.

210
00:16:31.222 --> 00:16:32.682
I knew you would.

211
00:16:40.273 --> 00:16:43.318
- Mama.
- Haniwa.

212
00:16:43.401 --> 00:16:45.153
Oh. my girl.

213
00:16:48.239 --> 00:16:52.285
- I thought you were dead.
- It's all right. You're safe now.

214
00:16:52.368 --> 00:16:54.871
I found you. I found you.

215
00:16:54.954 --> 00:16:56.206
Maghra.

216
00:16:57.290 --> 00:16:59.792
You didn't tell me we were having company.

217
00:17:03.004 --> 00:17:04.005
Baba.

218
00:17:06.132 --> 00:17:08.927
This is Lord Harlan.

219
00:17:09.761 --> 00:17:13.723
- This is his house.
- Honey. please. Our house.

220
00:17:14.974 --> 00:17:18.436
- What?
- Baba. Listen to me.

221
00:17:18.520 --> 00:17:21.606
Baba? This is Baba Voss?

222
00:17:22.106 --> 00:17:23.525
- I am.
- Huh.

223
00:17:24.817 --> 00:17:27.529
I'm Harlan. Lord of Pennsa.

224
00:17:28.905 --> 00:17:31.908
and this is awkward.
but I'm married to your wife.

225
00:17:32.492 --> 00:17:34.661
Baba. Come upstairs.

226
00:17:34.744 --> 00:17:38.289
- What is he talking about?
- Come upstairs. and I'll explain.

227
00:17:39.332 --> 00:17:40.333
Come.

228
00:17:40.416 --> 00:17:43.002
Yeah. let's all go upstairs.
Have a hot tea.

229
00:17:43.086 --> 00:17:46.130
You... You're gonna stop speaking.

230
00:17:46.714 --> 00:17:49.008
- Pretty unlikely.
- Not if I tear your throat out.

231
00:17:49.092 --> 00:17:51.094
And make our wife a widow?

232
00:17:51.177 --> 00:17:54.264
So. this is Baba Voss?

233
00:17:55.348 --> 00:17:56.349
Who is that?

234
00:17:57.392 --> 00:18:00.936
"Who's that?" Only your queen. that's all.

235
00:18:02.437 --> 00:18:04.941
Welcome. Baba Voss.

236
00:18:06.776 --> 00:18:09.028
And did I hear my sister call
Haniwa's name?

237
00:18:11.281 --> 00:18:12.282
Huh?

238
00:18:12.365 --> 00:18:13.950
<i>Please.</i>

239
00:18:14.908 --> 00:18:16.618
I'm Haniwa.

240
00:18:31.551 --> 00:18:33.428
My prayers have been answered.

241
00:18:35.180 --> 00:18:38.016
My sister's family
returned to her unharmed.

242
00:18:39.309 --> 00:18:42.228
My babies.

243
00:18:44.189 --> 00:18:48.026
You must all join me for dinner.
We must toast your safe return.

244
00:18:55.992 --> 00:18:57.493
You think she means right now?

245
00:19:00.497 --> 00:19:02.957
The mighty Baba Voss.

246
00:19:05.752 --> 00:19:08.588
Your legend precedes you.
and you did not disappoint.

247
00:19:09.088 --> 00:19:12.175
You walked through my guards
like they were nothing but tall weeds.

248
00:19:12.717 --> 00:19:14.219
They didn't seem very tall.

249
00:19:16.679 --> 00:19:18.765
Some of the world's finest soldiers.

250
00:19:19.265 --> 00:19:22.145
You send them to hunt children.
There's no wonder they can't fight a man.

251
00:19:22.227 --> 00:19:24.229
Baba.

252
00:19:25.563 --> 00:19:26.898
It's fine. Maghra.

253
00:19:28.066 --> 00:19:30.193
He needn't be polite on my account.

254
00:19:30.276 --> 00:19:32.570
After all. we're all family here.
are we not?

255
00:19:32.654 --> 00:19:34.239
- Hear. hear.
- Mmm.

256
00:19:35.657 --> 00:19:40.537
Besides. as a former
Trivantian soldier and a Slaver.

257
00:19:40.620 --> 00:19:43.540
it's only fair to expect
a certain lack of table manners.

258
00:19:43.623 --> 00:19:44.874
Sibeth. please.

259
00:19:44.958 --> 00:19:47.836
Wait... You're a Slaver?

260
00:19:48.837 --> 00:19:51.798
Seriously? Wow.

261
00:19:52.549 --> 00:19:54.634
I mean. not that I'm judging. but...

262
00:19:55.510 --> 00:19:58.263
- No. I am judging. A lot.
- You be quiet.

263
00:19:58.346 --> 00:20:00.265
Yes. Harlan.

264
00:20:00.932 --> 00:20:04.102
Be very quiet. Like a little mouse.

265
00:20:04.185 --> 00:20:05.770
I just find it so wonderfully ironic

266
00:20:05.854 --> 00:20:10.692
that a Payan princess would marry
a Slaver out of all people.

267
00:20:10.775 --> 00:20:12.694
Though I suppose
Jerlamarel didn't leave you

268
00:20:12.777 --> 00:20:15.154
much of a choice now. did he. Maghra?

269
00:20:15.238 --> 00:20:16.489
Abandoning you like that?

270
00:20:17.156 --> 00:20:19.158
Oh. I apologize. Lord Harlan…

271
00:20:19.242 --> 00:20:21.703
…for discussing your wife's ex-lovers
in front of you.

272
00:20:21.786 --> 00:20:25.540
No. it's fine. It's fine.
We all have our pasts. don't we?

273
00:20:26.457 --> 00:20:29.669
For instance. this used to be my house.
Now it's yours.

274
00:20:30.170 --> 00:20:32.547
And the great dance continues.

275
00:20:32.630 --> 00:20:34.716
Mmm. you make an interesting point.

276
00:20:35.842 --> 00:20:38.720
Since my birthright determined
my future from a young age.

277
00:20:38.803 --> 00:20:42.056
I have no excitingly
scandalous past to speak of.

278
00:20:42.140 --> 00:20:46.978
I suppose I envied Maghra. in a way.

279
00:20:48.313 --> 00:20:49.439
The freedom.

280
00:20:50.023 --> 00:20:52.942
selfish as it seemed.
to choose her own path

281
00:20:53.026 --> 00:20:56.946
with no regard for others.
no sense of responsibility for anyone...

282
00:20:57.030 --> 00:21:01.367
Respectfully. Your Majesty.
Maghra has devoted her life

283
00:21:01.451 --> 00:21:05.330
to loving her husband.
raising her children.

284
00:21:05.413 --> 00:21:07.707
and serving the Alkenny people.

285
00:21:07.790 --> 00:21:10.418
Respectfully. mountain woman…

286
00:21:11.961 --> 00:21:15.632
it is because of my sister that
the Alkenny are traitors to the crown.

287
00:21:15.715 --> 00:21:17.592
The Alkenny cannot be traitors
to the crown.

288
00:21:17.675 --> 00:21:19.260
The Alkenny people are no more.

289
00:21:19.344 --> 00:21:21.947
If a hidden tribe disappears.
how are we to even know?

290
00:21:21.971 --> 00:21:23.097
Enough.

291
00:21:27.101 --> 00:21:28.746
Our father forbade the discussion

292
00:21:28.770 --> 00:21:32.482
of politics at the table
for a very good reason.

293
00:21:32.565 --> 00:21:33.983
Well said. my dear.

294
00:21:34.484 --> 00:21:38.071
- Who'd like more wine?
- Mmm. I would.

295
00:21:39.072 --> 00:21:40.073
It's funny.

296
00:21:40.782 --> 00:21:44.494
When we were children. I was the romantic.

297
00:21:45.912 --> 00:21:48.915
Maghra always swore she'd never marry.
and yet. here we are.

298
00:21:49.624 --> 00:21:52.710
I'm the spinster. and she has
two husbands at this table alone.

299
00:21:55.964 --> 00:21:58.007
I meant no offense. Baba Voss.

300
00:21:58.091 --> 00:21:59.843
I love my sister dearly.

301
00:21:59.926 --> 00:22:02.929
even though she's lied to me.
betrayed me.

302
00:22:03.012 --> 00:22:04.323
<i>You are my husband. I love only you.</i>

303
00:22:04.347 --> 00:22:06.599
I would still kill or die for her.

304
00:22:07.308 --> 00:22:09.269
I imagine it's the same with you.

305
00:22:10.270 --> 00:22:12.814
Oh. and you. of course. Lord Harlan. Mmm.

306
00:22:12.897 --> 00:22:15.775
It's an honor to be in such fine company.

307
00:23:21.716 --> 00:23:24.219
Do you recognize my voice. soldier?

308
00:23:38.274 --> 00:23:41.361
I couldn't possibly because you're dead.

309
00:23:42.737 --> 00:23:44.155
Only on the inside.

310
00:23:49.118 --> 00:23:51.204
The queen said you took your own life.

311
00:23:52.997 --> 00:23:58.002
The queen has always had
a troubled relationship with the truth.

312
00:23:58.086 --> 00:23:59.420
wouldn't you say?

313
00:24:02.257 --> 00:24:03.508
Not out loud.

314
00:24:10.557 --> 00:24:15.562
So… what happens now?

315
00:24:19.107 --> 00:24:20.358
What indeed?

316
00:24:30.118 --> 00:24:31.870
<i>Kofun. Haniwa.</i>

317
00:24:32.787 --> 00:24:36.499
you must know your mother
never stopped searching for you.

318
00:24:36.583 --> 00:24:40.378
From the moment you were separated.
you were all she thought of.

319
00:24:41.713 --> 00:24:45.300
It's unfortunate she must go
on a journey now just as you've arrived.

320
00:24:45.383 --> 00:24:47.343
- I wish it were different.
- Journey?

321
00:24:47.427 --> 00:24:48.428
What journey?

322
00:24:48.511 --> 00:24:51.431
- What is she talking about?
- I didn't get a chance to tell you...

323
00:24:51.514 --> 00:24:53.683
It's a mission of the utmost importance.

324
00:24:55.018 --> 00:24:56.895
Maghra will serve as my emissary

325
00:24:56.978 --> 00:24:59.606
to receive a peace delegation
from Trivantes.

326
00:24:59.689 --> 00:25:01.608
You're leaving now?

327
00:25:01.691 --> 00:25:05.195
It's only for a few days. I... I have to.

328
00:25:05.278 --> 00:25:06.654
- I'm coming with you.
- Me too.

329
00:25:06.738 --> 00:25:08.531
- No.
- No.

330
00:25:09.449 --> 00:25:11.576
You're members of the royal family.

331
00:25:12.118 --> 00:25:14.954
Too valuable a prize
for the Trivantians to pass up.

332
00:25:16.122 --> 00:25:17.916
They wouldn't even know we were there.

333
00:25:19.125 --> 00:25:23.546
You're the future of this kingdom
and quite possibly the world.

334
00:25:23.630 --> 00:25:25.757
We cannot risk any harm coming to you.

335
00:25:25.840 --> 00:25:28.051
My sister is right. You will stay here.

336
00:25:28.134 --> 00:25:30.470
I just got you back.
I will not lose you again.

337
00:25:30.553 --> 00:25:33.890
- Mama.
- Haniwa. Your mother has spoken.

338
00:25:33.973 --> 00:25:37.602
Maghra. the Trivantians will not send
a peace delegation.

339
00:25:37.685 --> 00:25:39.312
They do not negotiate.

340
00:25:39.395 --> 00:25:43.566
I wouldn't call it a negotiation.
They're going to grovel.

341
00:25:43.650 --> 00:25:46.402
The Trivantians have never groveled.
and they never will.

342
00:25:47.278 --> 00:25:49.531
They've never had
a truly worthy adversary.

343
00:25:50.365 --> 00:25:52.492
- You?
- God.

344
00:25:54.160 --> 00:25:57.288
Their soldiers will slit your god's throat
and drink its blood.

345
00:25:57.372 --> 00:26:00.041
Yet it is the Trivantians
who have sued for peace.

346
00:26:00.124 --> 00:26:01.668
It is a trick or a trap.

347
00:26:01.751 --> 00:26:04.796
Baba. we have to try.
If there's even a chance...

348
00:26:04.879 --> 00:26:06.047
There is not.

349
00:26:06.130 --> 00:26:08.025
Then we'll defeat them on the battlefield.

350
00:26:08.049 --> 00:26:10.885
- There is even less chance of that.
- So what would you have us do?

351
00:26:10.969 --> 00:26:14.681
The Trivantians are consumed with
the war with the Ganites to the west.

352
00:26:14.764 --> 00:26:16.604
Do nothing to draw
their attention to the east.

353
00:26:16.641 --> 00:26:18.685
- What if it's too late for that?
- Then surrender.

354
00:26:18.768 --> 00:26:20.353
Spoken like a true Trivantian.

355
00:26:39.497 --> 00:26:41.708
You must understand.

356
00:26:41.791 --> 00:26:44.752
I needed him to keep us safe.

357
00:26:44.836 --> 00:26:46.838
That little worm down there
doesn't think so.

358
00:26:47.547 --> 00:26:49.048
That's just his manner.

359
00:26:50.300 --> 00:26:54.137
Baba. You've always trusted me.

360
00:26:57.140 --> 00:26:59.100
And you have lied to me for all that time.

361
00:26:59.601 --> 00:27:03.062
Well. you of all people know the pain
of a past best forgotten.

362
00:27:04.606 --> 00:27:06.691
You were happy to be reminded. Princess.

363
00:27:08.151 --> 00:27:10.695
The princess who ran away from Paya died

364
00:27:10.778 --> 00:27:13.865
the day I pledged myself
to you as your wife.

365
00:27:13.948 --> 00:27:15.491
Then let us leave this place.

366
00:27:16.868 --> 00:27:19.162
Let us take our children
and return to the mountains.

367
00:27:19.245 --> 00:27:21.831
We were happy there. We can be again.

368
00:27:21.915 --> 00:27:24.876
- If only it were that simple.
- It is that simple.

369
00:27:24.959 --> 00:27:28.588
You are my wife. they are our children.
and this is the past you wish to forget.

370
00:27:28.671 --> 00:27:30.673
Well. these are my father's people.

371
00:27:33.468 --> 00:27:39.182
He begged me on his deathbed
to protect them from my sister.

372
00:27:39.265 --> 00:27:40.725
and I failed him.

373
00:27:42.352 --> 00:27:46.648
I abandoned Paya.
and so many died at Sibeth's hands.

374
00:27:50.944 --> 00:27:55.281
I'm the only one who can
truly challenge her for the throne

375
00:27:55.365 --> 00:27:57.033
and save the kingdom.

376
00:27:59.452 --> 00:28:01.621
So princess isn't good enough.

377
00:28:02.872 --> 00:28:04.666
Now you wish to be queen?

378
00:28:04.749 --> 00:28:07.627
Only until I've ensured a lasting peace.

379
00:28:07.710 --> 00:28:10.088
and then I'll hand power over to Harlan.

380
00:28:10.171 --> 00:28:13.633
Maghra. Harlan is making you his tool.

381
00:28:14.217 --> 00:28:17.846
No. I have made him mine.

382
00:28:19.597 --> 00:28:22.225
You are forgetting
what is most important to you.

383
00:28:22.308 --> 00:28:25.687
You. me. Haniwa. Kofun.
we are what matter most.

384
00:28:25.770 --> 00:28:27.480
I would die for my children.

385
00:28:27.564 --> 00:28:30.733
I'm not asking you to die for them.
I'm asking you to live for them.

386
00:28:30.817 --> 00:28:31.818
If I run off...

387
00:28:32.610 --> 00:28:35.363
If I run off.
if I turn my sister against me again.

388
00:28:35.446 --> 00:28:39.242
Haniwa and Kofun won't
be safe anywhere ever.

389
00:28:40.827 --> 00:28:44.956
I have kept us safe for 18 years.
I can protect us out there.

390
00:28:45.039 --> 00:28:47.625
- I cannot do that here.
- I know. but I can.

391
00:28:48.168 --> 00:28:51.171
I can protect them and you.

392
00:28:51.254 --> 00:28:54.048
Oh. good. Good. you're both here.

393
00:28:54.132 --> 00:28:57.635
Now. let's talk
about sleeping arrangements.

394
00:28:58.261 --> 00:29:01.139
Now. obviously.
in the usual circumstances.

395
00:29:01.222 --> 00:29:03.308
I am open to group activities.

396
00:29:03.391 --> 00:29:05.643
- Harlan.
- Why do you think my bed is so big?

397
00:29:05.727 --> 00:29:07.020
Stop it.

398
00:29:08.688 --> 00:29:10.148
Forgive me.

399
00:29:10.231 --> 00:29:14.944
Just trying to make the best
of a delicate situation.

400
00:29:17.238 --> 00:29:20.700
You even tell him this is my house?
This is my house.

401
00:29:22.452 --> 00:29:23.536
No one cares.

402
00:29:24.329 --> 00:29:25.663
You're drunk.

403
00:29:26.748 --> 00:29:27.874
Yes.

404
00:29:29.000 --> 00:29:31.169
And with good reason. I think.

405
00:29:32.086 --> 00:29:34.422
Look. Baba... Bab... Voss.

406
00:29:34.506 --> 00:29:38.218
I don't care what you do in here
with my wife... Our wife.

407
00:29:38.760 --> 00:29:40.220
Doesn't matter.

408
00:29:40.303 --> 00:29:45.808
But it will be bad for all of us
if people were to find out.

409
00:29:47.018 --> 00:29:50.355
Secret alliances only work
if they stay secret.

410
00:29:50.438 --> 00:29:51.439
If he keeps talking.

411
00:29:51.523 --> 00:29:53.358
- I'm going to feed him his own throat.
- Shh.

412
00:29:53.441 --> 00:29:55.318
Is he like this with everybody?

413
00:29:55.401 --> 00:29:57.570
Leave us. please.

414
00:30:00.740 --> 00:30:01.741
As you wish.

415
00:30:04.160 --> 00:30:05.912
You know. in time. Baba Voss.

416
00:30:05.995 --> 00:30:08.498
you will come to realize
I'm not your enemy.

417
00:30:09.290 --> 00:30:12.085
but that makes me no less dangerous.

418
00:30:14.504 --> 00:30:17.841
I may have lost my house.
but this is still my city.

419
00:30:17.924 --> 00:30:20.969
And you would be well advised
to watch how you speak to me.

420
00:30:36.025 --> 00:30:39.654
I need you. Now more than ever.

421
00:30:47.996 --> 00:30:48.997
Baba?

422
00:30:53.042 --> 00:30:54.627
What did they do to you?

423
00:30:56.588 --> 00:30:58.089
I had to get her back.

424
00:31:10.810 --> 00:31:13.188
<i>I honestly don't know
what the queen's thinking.</i>

425
00:31:13.688 --> 00:31:15.565
Witches in the royal family?

426
00:31:15.648 --> 00:31:19.152
Does she think the people will stand for
it? There will be rioting at her gates...

427
00:31:19.235 --> 00:31:21.821
Lower your voice.
or the queen will have your tongue.

428
00:31:30.038 --> 00:31:31.915
Presage.

429
00:31:31.998 --> 00:31:33.374
Is that you?

430
00:31:38.004 --> 00:31:39.797
I am called Paris.

431
00:31:41.341 --> 00:31:42.509
Paris.

432
00:31:44.427 --> 00:31:46.638
I have an urgent message for the princess.

433
00:31:56.856 --> 00:31:59.526
You're the soldier
who brought Kofun to Pennsa.

434
00:32:00.610 --> 00:32:01.611
Yes.

435
00:32:02.612 --> 00:32:05.031
He told me the others were less inclined.

436
00:32:07.200 --> 00:32:09.285
We had our orders. I followed them.

437
00:32:10.119 --> 00:32:13.248
And now. whose orders do you follow?

438
00:32:13.331 --> 00:32:18.169
For 20 years. I have sworn
my allegiance to the Witchfinder general.

439
00:32:19.504 --> 00:32:21.130
Not an easy habit to break.

440
00:32:24.092 --> 00:32:27.011
I will make sure Mag...
The princess gets this.

441
00:32:30.056 --> 00:32:32.183
That day. in the woods.

442
00:32:33.852 --> 00:32:35.228
You touched me.

443
00:32:37.647 --> 00:32:40.108
I wonder what it must feel like

444
00:32:40.191 --> 00:32:43.361
to know things that will happen
before they occur.

445
00:32:46.698 --> 00:32:51.286
Mainly it means I'm always concerned.

446
00:32:55.498 --> 00:32:57.917
Never thought of it like that.

447
00:32:59.043 --> 00:33:01.129
Speaking of those concerns…

448
00:33:06.259 --> 00:33:10.388
You protected Kofun before.
Do the same now.

449
00:33:11.472 --> 00:33:15.560
Stay close to him
and keep him away from trouble.

450
00:33:17.729 --> 00:33:22.192
I pulled him into this world.
He is past listening to me.

451
00:33:27.238 --> 00:33:28.740
I will do as you ask.

452
00:33:29.866 --> 00:33:32.660
Good. Good. Thank you.

453
00:33:32.744 --> 00:33:33.745
But…

454
00:33:35.371 --> 00:33:38.124
only because it is you doing the asking.

455
00:33:44.964 --> 00:33:46.716
You are called Toad?

456
00:33:46.799 --> 00:33:48.092
Yes.

457
00:33:48.176 --> 00:33:49.969
That is a stupid name.

458
00:33:50.929 --> 00:33:53.556
A failure of imagination
on the part of my parents.

459
00:33:57.977 --> 00:33:58.978
Wait here.

460
00:34:41.688 --> 00:34:43.106
Princess Maghra.

461
00:34:47.318 --> 00:34:49.237
I hear a dead man speaking.

462
00:34:53.992 --> 00:34:55.702
Then listen closer.

463
00:34:59.080 --> 00:35:00.373
Is it really you?

464
00:35:04.252 --> 00:35:05.378
Tamacti.

465
00:35:06.545 --> 00:35:10.300
I hear congratulations are in order.
There was a wedding?

466
00:35:12.259 --> 00:35:15.929
Yes. While you were dead.
I've been trying to fix things.

467
00:35:16.014 --> 00:35:17.473
By marrying a lord?

468
00:35:17.556 --> 00:35:22.853
The Pennsan soldiers are loyal
to Harlan first and the queen second.

469
00:35:24.605 --> 00:35:25.607
That's good.

470
00:35:26.774 --> 00:35:30.111
We'll need all the forces we can get
if we're going to overcome your sister.

471
00:35:30.195 --> 00:35:33.114
We're all in agreement.
Harlan is a valuable asset.

472
00:35:33.198 --> 00:35:35.408
- When do we move?
- I'm working as fast as I can.

473
00:35:35.491 --> 00:35:37.371
Explaining why I'm not dead
when I killed myself

474
00:35:37.409 --> 00:35:39.346
in the service of the queen
is proving complicated.

475
00:35:39.370 --> 00:35:41.371
- How much time?
- More than we have.

476
00:35:41.456 --> 00:35:45.835
From what I hear. your sister is days away
from marching Paya into war.

477
00:35:46.335 --> 00:35:47.629
Perhaps not.

478
00:35:47.712 --> 00:35:51.090
I convinced her to let me arrange
a diplomatic summit with Trivantes.

479
00:35:51.174 --> 00:35:52.926
Why would the Trivantians discuss peace

480
00:35:53.009 --> 00:35:54.889
when they never declared war
in the first place?

481
00:35:54.928 --> 00:35:56.054
It's a delay.

482
00:35:56.137 --> 00:35:58.598
To allow the soldiers
to march from the western front.

483
00:35:58.681 --> 00:36:03.019
You said yourself the Trivantians
are heavily occupied on the western front.

484
00:36:03.102 --> 00:36:05.647
Well. they can't possibly
want war in the east.

485
00:36:06.648 --> 00:36:11.236
There may very well be a chance for peace
even if they do have ulterior motives.

486
00:36:11.319 --> 00:36:15.490
As long as your sister is on the throne.
there will be no peace.

487
00:36:17.742 --> 00:36:23.790
However. killing the queen.
or even deposing her. is no simple matter.

488
00:36:24.749 --> 00:36:29.128
There are many laws in the strands
all designed to protect the monarch.

489
00:36:29.212 --> 00:36:31.548
- And you know all these laws?
- No. Not all.

490
00:36:31.631 --> 00:36:32.674
I do.

491
00:36:33.758 --> 00:36:37.053
So you gather your Witchfinders.
and you let me worry about the laws.

492
00:36:37.136 --> 00:36:38.388
Do you have a plan?

493
00:36:39.848 --> 00:36:40.849
More than one.

494
00:36:44.143 --> 00:36:46.187
So different from how we grew up.

495
00:36:46.271 --> 00:36:49.983
You should see Trivantes.
It makes Pennsa look tiny.

496
00:36:50.066 --> 00:36:51.985
It's an incredible place.

497
00:36:53.862 --> 00:36:57.365
Except for the slaves
and how they kidnapped you.

498
00:36:58.825 --> 00:37:00.535
- Not all Trivantians are bad.
- Ow.

499
00:37:05.874 --> 00:37:09.627
I met someone there. Someone like us.

500
00:37:12.255 --> 00:37:14.549
- Really?
- Yes.

501
00:37:16.217 --> 00:37:19.762
And no relation to Jerlamarel.
Both of her parents are blind.

502
00:37:21.681 --> 00:37:23.766
So it's not just Jerlamarel's line.

503
00:37:25.685 --> 00:37:27.145
Sight's really coming back.

504
00:37:27.854 --> 00:37:29.355
You don't sound too happy about it.

505
00:37:29.439 --> 00:37:31.316
Look at what it's done to the world.

506
00:37:32.108 --> 00:37:33.276
Look what it's done to us.

507
00:37:33.359 --> 00:37:35.445
It wasn't vision that destroyed the world.

508
00:37:36.905 --> 00:37:38.198
It was people.

509
00:37:40.074 --> 00:37:41.868
They can do that with or without sight.

510
00:37:42.493 --> 00:37:44.704
Look at the queen waging war on Trivantes.

511
00:37:44.787 --> 00:37:48.625
She's protecting her people.
Isn't that what queens do?

512
00:37:48.708 --> 00:37:51.419
Why are you defending someone
who hunted us our whole lives?

513
00:37:51.503 --> 00:37:53.338
She didn't know we were family.

514
00:37:54.506 --> 00:37:56.966
If Mom had spoken up.
maybe we wouldn't have had to hide.

515
00:37:57.050 --> 00:37:58.384
Mom was protecting us.

516
00:38:00.762 --> 00:38:01.763
Maybe.

517
00:38:03.765 --> 00:38:05.433
Maybe she was protecting herself.

518
00:38:06.434 --> 00:38:08.686
I would trust our mother
over the queen any day.

519
00:38:09.646 --> 00:38:11.231
What about Jerlamarel?

520
00:38:11.731 --> 00:38:15.485
You trusted him.
And Boots. you vouched for him too.

521
00:38:17.403 --> 00:38:20.281
Do you really want to taunt me
while I have a blade to your scalp?

522
00:38:21.908 --> 00:38:23.117
Sorry.

523
00:38:28.206 --> 00:38:29.249
I am too.

524
00:38:32.126 --> 00:38:33.253
For everything.

525
00:38:37.674 --> 00:38:42.095
All right. Are you sure about this?

526
00:38:43.096 --> 00:38:44.138
Do it.

527
00:38:59.737 --> 00:39:02.282
- Paris?
- Yeah. Here. Come.

528
00:39:03.825 --> 00:39:04.826
Sit.

529
00:39:06.619 --> 00:39:09.247
Sit with me. Hmm.

530
00:39:11.082 --> 00:39:14.752
So. a shift in the world.

531
00:39:15.753 --> 00:39:17.005
Yes.

532
00:39:21.259 --> 00:39:24.095
I'm sorry.

533
00:39:27.223 --> 00:39:29.934
I'm sorry I didn't tell you
about all of this.

534
00:39:31.644 --> 00:39:33.271
About who I really was.

535
00:39:34.647 --> 00:39:39.235
Maghra. I know who you really are.

536
00:39:41.613 --> 00:39:42.864
Mmm?

537
00:39:42.947 --> 00:39:47.619
As for this.
I am glad you did not tell me.

538
00:39:48.536 --> 00:39:51.080
I would not have kept
your secret from Baba.

539
00:39:51.956 --> 00:39:53.583
He's so angry.

540
00:39:54.834 --> 00:39:56.753
And how would you have him be?

541
00:39:57.754 --> 00:40:01.508
Finding his wife married to another?

542
00:40:02.634 --> 00:40:04.177
I've explained that.

543
00:40:05.887 --> 00:40:10.808
Did you explain to him why you concealed

544
00:40:10.892 --> 00:40:13.353
that you were a daughter of Kane?

545
00:40:15.522 --> 00:40:17.357
He doesn't wanna listen to me.

546
00:40:18.900 --> 00:40:23.363
I can't run away from this.
I have to stay.

547
00:40:24.489 --> 00:40:26.241
For Haniwa and Kofun.

548
00:40:27.992 --> 00:40:30.495
You stay for Haniwa and Kofun?

549
00:40:30.995 --> 00:40:32.330
Who else?

550
00:40:36.251 --> 00:40:38.127
The crown is your birthright.

551
00:40:41.047 --> 00:40:43.299
It is no small thing to wear it.

552
00:40:52.392 --> 00:40:53.393
You know…

553
00:40:57.063 --> 00:40:59.566
it was you who started this whole journey.

554
00:41:02.110 --> 00:41:05.989
You who taught Haniwa and Kofun to read.

555
00:41:07.824 --> 00:41:11.494
Told them the tales
of the great Jerlamarel.

556
00:41:14.247 --> 00:41:15.415
Their father.

557
00:41:19.085 --> 00:41:21.171
I would never have left the mountains.

558
00:41:27.093 --> 00:41:29.179
It was only a matter of time.

559
00:41:30.680 --> 00:41:33.516
The mountains could never contain you.

560
00:41:40.899 --> 00:41:42.317
I've missed you.

561
00:41:44.194 --> 00:41:45.403
Mmm.

562
00:41:48.031 --> 00:41:49.032
Mmm.

563
00:42:12.805 --> 00:42:15.934
Kofun.

564
00:42:16.726 --> 00:42:17.977
What are you doing out here?

565
00:42:19.896 --> 00:42:21.606
Listening to the world.

566
00:42:21.689 --> 00:42:24.067
What do you hear?

567
00:42:26.277 --> 00:42:28.112
Everything. Come.

568
00:42:31.574 --> 00:42:34.369
Close those eyes of yours.

569
00:42:35.995 --> 00:42:37.705
Let the sound fill your mind.

570
00:42:42.669 --> 00:42:45.588
Now. what do you hear?

571
00:42:48.967 --> 00:42:50.343
Nothing really.

572
00:42:50.844 --> 00:42:52.595
Nothing is never nothing.

573
00:42:53.221 --> 00:42:55.223
Even the absence of sound is telling.

574
00:43:01.354 --> 00:43:03.147
Dad.

575
00:43:03.231 --> 00:43:06.276
Shh. I know. I heard him come.

576
00:43:07.277 --> 00:43:08.653
Just relax.

577
00:43:10.363 --> 00:43:12.615
He's breathing slow. He's not on the hunt.

578
00:43:16.035 --> 00:43:19.956
There. He's gone to rejoin the others.

579
00:43:27.046 --> 00:43:28.423
Are you angry at Mom?

580
00:43:34.762 --> 00:43:37.348
What your mother does.
she is doing for you and your sister.

581
00:43:40.602 --> 00:43:42.020
And what about for you?

582
00:43:49.110 --> 00:43:51.696
I was sure you'd throw Harlan
off the roof when you arrived.

583
00:43:53.990 --> 00:43:55.241
I considered it.

584
00:44:00.038 --> 00:44:01.623
You can't let Harlan win.

585
00:44:04.667 --> 00:44:06.002
Harlan doesn't matter.

586
00:44:07.462 --> 00:44:09.088
This whole place doesn't matter.

587
00:44:10.340 --> 00:44:11.716
We are together again.

588
00:44:14.385 --> 00:44:16.846
I just have to figure out
how to get out of this place.

589
00:44:17.931 --> 00:44:19.349
Back to where we belong.

590
00:44:22.268 --> 00:44:24.729
I can't think of any place
where we all belong anymore.

591
00:44:41.621 --> 00:44:42.914
Wait. I hear it.

592
00:44:44.916 --> 00:44:45.917
Tell me.

593
00:44:58.429 --> 00:44:59.430
Yeah?

594
00:44:59.514 --> 00:45:02.194
Lord Harlan. your brother's horse
was found running in the orchards.

595
00:45:02.225 --> 00:45:03.977
Saddled and riderless.

596
00:45:05.311 --> 00:45:07.105
Well. it wouldn't be the first time.

597
00:45:07.939 --> 00:45:11.734
Kerrigan has a habit of grabbing
the nearest horse when he's in a rush.

598
00:45:13.069 --> 00:45:16.281
Look. um. put her in my stables.
He'll pick her up when he's home.

599
00:45:16.781 --> 00:45:21.828
Sir. this satchel hung on the saddle
with a message for you.

600
00:45:46.936 --> 00:45:48.188
Oh. no.

601
00:45:50.648 --> 00:45:51.649
No.

602
00:46:27.602 --> 00:46:30.271
What happened?

603
00:46:41.449 --> 00:46:43.576
What is it? What happened?

604
00:46:45.203 --> 00:46:46.830
Kerri.

605
00:46:48.331 --> 00:46:49.582
Kerrigan.

606
00:46:51.334 --> 00:46:52.627
I'm so sorry.

607
00:47:10.311 --> 00:47:11.312
Kofun?

608
00:47:12.730 --> 00:47:14.774
Ah. How are you settling in?

609
00:47:15.984 --> 00:47:17.235
Very well. thank you.

610
00:47:25.326 --> 00:47:26.536
Would you like some?

611
00:47:29.706 --> 00:47:30.707
Sure.

612
00:47:48.641 --> 00:47:52.312
Your mother. This house.

613
00:47:53.563 --> 00:47:55.356
It must be a lot to take in.

614
00:47:57.108 --> 00:47:59.485
It is.

615
00:48:15.960 --> 00:48:17.378
Something troubling you?

616
00:48:18.421 --> 00:48:21.716
I forgot for a moment you were sighted.

617
00:48:24.469 --> 00:48:27.889
I imagine you're able to see my pain?

618
00:48:29.390 --> 00:48:30.391
Yes.

619
00:48:32.185 --> 00:48:33.895
What a gift that must be.

620
00:48:38.775 --> 00:48:41.736
It also means I have no choice
but to trust you.

621
00:48:43.154 --> 00:48:44.781
Because it's a secret.

622
00:48:45.865 --> 00:48:46.866
Kofun.

623
00:48:48.660 --> 00:48:50.078
It must stay between us.

624
00:48:50.995 --> 00:48:53.206
Of course. It will.

625
00:49:05.134 --> 00:49:06.678
I lost the baby.

626
00:49:13.893 --> 00:49:15.478
He was taken from me.

627
00:49:17.856 --> 00:49:19.190
I'm so sorry.

628
00:49:28.241 --> 00:49:29.742
When the people find out...

629
00:49:29.826 --> 00:49:33.496
In our village. it happened all the time.
People will understand.

630
00:49:35.415 --> 00:49:36.916
This is not your village.

631
00:49:38.168 --> 00:49:40.128
And I'm not an Alkenny mother.

632
00:49:40.211 --> 00:49:43.173
I stood before the entire city
and announced my child.

633
00:49:43.256 --> 00:49:45.800
A sighted child who now will not come.

634
00:49:48.178 --> 00:49:51.598
They'll think I'm... I'm no longer chosen.

635
00:49:52.932 --> 00:49:54.767
That I'm no longer God's queen.

636
00:49:56.060 --> 00:49:57.228
So tell them the truth.

637
00:49:59.314 --> 00:50:03.443
They will understand.
They will feel for you. just like I do.

638
00:50:03.526 --> 00:50:04.986
I... I'm sorry.

639
00:50:05.069 --> 00:50:06.154
Thank you.

640
00:50:07.113 --> 00:50:10.325
Thank you. Kofun.

641
00:50:14.704 --> 00:50:19.167
I'll confess. I came here because
I needed to open my heart to someone.

642
00:50:21.628 --> 00:50:24.756
I felt strongly that I could trust you.

643
00:50:26.090 --> 00:50:27.675
I felt that from the moment we met.

644
00:50:28.760 --> 00:50:30.845
Do you feel you can trust me?

645
00:50:36.476 --> 00:50:37.477
I don't know.

646
00:50:40.772 --> 00:50:43.525
Because my Witchfinders
killed your people?

647
00:50:43.608 --> 00:50:44.609
Yes.

648
00:50:49.030 --> 00:50:51.533
I hope I can help you understand

649
00:50:51.616 --> 00:50:56.246
that if I'd known it was
Maghra and her children.

650
00:50:56.871 --> 00:50:58.122
I...

651
00:50:59.290 --> 00:51:01.793
- I don't want you to hate me. Kofun.
- I don't know you.

652
00:51:01.876 --> 00:51:04.629
But I want you to! I want you to know me.

653
00:51:05.922 --> 00:51:07.924
Being queen is very lonely.

654
00:51:11.344 --> 00:51:15.223
I've been alone for so long.
I feared I lost the ability to connect.

655
00:51:16.850 --> 00:51:19.018
But I already feel connected to you.

656
00:51:19.602 --> 00:51:23.690
There's something about you
that soothes me.

657
00:51:24.482 --> 00:51:26.234
That fills me with hope.

658
00:51:28.653 --> 00:51:29.654
Hope for what?

659
00:51:30.446 --> 00:51:31.948
The future of Paya.

660
00:51:32.782 --> 00:51:34.450
I'll not live forever.

661
00:51:34.534 --> 00:51:39.873
This holy kingdom may someday rest
on your shoulders.

662
00:51:40.498 --> 00:51:43.459
It is too much weight
for any mortal woman or man.

663
00:51:44.002 --> 00:51:49.090
I have only borne it because
through all my years on the throne.

664
00:51:49.174 --> 00:51:54.095
there's always been somebody at my side.
inside of me…

665
00:51:56.681 --> 00:51:58.933
guiding my every move.

666
00:51:59.767 --> 00:52:02.562
- Are you talking about God?
- Yes. Kofun.

667
00:52:03.229 --> 00:52:05.064
Without whom. we are dust.

668
00:52:07.108 --> 00:52:09.777
I will show you

669
00:52:09.861 --> 00:52:12.363
- how to seek God's counsel…
- Sibeth.

670
00:52:12.447 --> 00:52:14.574
…so that you will know her voice
when you need it.

671
00:52:14.657 --> 00:52:16.409
and she will know yours.

672
00:52:18.953 --> 00:52:23.166
Listen.
To hear her. you must first feel her.

673
00:52:30.173 --> 00:52:33.343
Let her flame warm you.
as the God Flame warms the earth.

674
00:52:33.426 --> 00:52:37.055
Oh. yes. Feel her.

675
00:52:37.805 --> 00:52:41.059
Ah. Yes.

676
00:52:41.142 --> 00:52:44.979
Feel me. Kofun.

677
00:52:45.063 --> 00:52:49.150
Lose yourself in me.
and you will find God.

678
00:52:49.234 --> 00:52:52.820
Yes. Feel me.

679
00:52:52.904 --> 00:52:55.740
Feel me.

680
00:53:05.440 --> 00:53:07.440
